quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  16,7,"And they bear your burdens to towns, which you could not reach except by straining yourselves. Indeed your Lord is most kind and merciful"
  16,8,"And horses, mules and asses, for you to ride them, and for pomp, and He creates what you do not know"
  16,9,"With Allah rests guidance to the straight path, and some of the paths are devious, and had He wished He would have guided you all"
  16,10,"It is He who sends down water from the sky: from it you get your drink and with it are [sustained] the plants wherein you pasture your herds"
  16,11,"For you He makes the crops grow with it and olives, date palms, vines, and fruits of all kinds. There is indeed a sign in that for a people who reflect"
  16,12,"He disposed the night and the day for you, and the sun, the moon and the stars are disposed by His command. There are indeed signs in that for people who exercise their reason"
  16,13,"And [He disposed for your benefit] whatever He has created for you in the earth of diverse huesâ€”there is indeed a sign in that for a people who take admonition"
  16,14,"It is He who disposed the sea [for your benefit] that you may eat from it fresh meat, and obtain from it ornaments which you wear, and you see the ships plowing through it, that you may seek His bounty and that you may give thanks"